<title>CANADA: Bundesbank's Hartmann sees 1.70 DM as &quot;adequate&quot;.</title>
<headline>Bundesbank's Hartmann sees 1.70 DM as &quot;adequate&quot;.</headline>
<dateline>TORONTO 1997-05-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>Bundesbank board member Wendelin Hartmann said on Friday that an exchange rate of 1.70 marks per U.S. dollar was adequate for both the United States and Germany.</p>
<p>&quot;One-seventy is more or less adequate to both countries,&quot; he told a press conference after speaking at a foreign exchange conference here.</p>
<p>He added that no help for the economy from an exchange rate move can be expected or is indeed required.</p>
<p>On German interest rates he saw no reason for a change from what he described as current &quot;low and reasonable&quot; levels.</p>
<p>((Reuters Toronto Bureau (416) 941-8100))</p>
